Quickstart Ansible With Virtual Machines
Guided by the tutorial in the link below
https://dev.to/tuvannguyen/quickstart-ansible-with-virtual-machines-5ep8

Requirement:
The working machine has Ubuntu 20.04.01 LTS as operating system.


## 1. Install VirtualBox
https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Linux_Downloads
possible issues:
How to Fix VirtualBox’s “Kernel Driver Not Installed (rc=-1908)”
I had to enter unsecure mode in BIOS 


## 2. Install Ansible
https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/installation_guide/installation_distros.html#installing-ansible-on-ubuntu

enter the following commands into the terminal:
$ sudo apt update
$ sudo apt install software-properties-common
$ sudo add-apt-repository --yes --update ppa:ansible/ansible
$ sudo apt install ansible

## 3. Create a vitrual machine (VM) and install Ubuntu 
https://ubuntu.com/download/server
+ install openSSH (you will be ask for it)
https://www.wikihow.com/Install-Ubuntu-on-VirtualBox
+ create an ssh key on your computer
+ add the public key to the created VMs

## 4. Set host-only adapter on the VM
https://dev.to/isabolic99/how-to-set-host-only-adapter-on-vm-virtual-box-2jka

### 5. checking the ip-adress
https://itsfoss.com/check-ip-address-ubuntu/

### 6. Add new user 
sudo useradd -m -G sudo -s /bin/bash testuser		#add user with home dir
sudo passwd testuser					#set password for testuser
sudo usermod -aG sudo testuser			#makes testuser sudo

### 7. Switch between users
su testuser	#switch to testuser

### 8. change groupe and owner of host to add ip-adress
sudo chgrp 'username' hosts 
sudo chgrp 'username' hosts

replace 'username'


Other helpful tutorials might be:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3RiVKs8GHYQ


